title: scissor_doors
body:
An uncommon type of door mounting most often found on customized automobiles. Whereas most factory hinges on modern cars cause the doors to open sideways/forward on the same horizontal plane, scissor doors open [i]upward[/i]/forward.

See Wikipedia entries on Lamborghini Countach "[1]":[/wiki_pages/24728#dtext-external-links], Diablo "[2]":[/wiki_pages/24728#dtext-external-links] and Murcielago "[3]":[/wiki_pages/24728#dtext-external-links] for famous examples of scissor doors. Lamborghini was such a prolific user of this joint on its most dramatic cars that initially, scissor doors were also known as "Lambo doors."

Not to be confused with [[gullwing doors]], which are hinged at the roof and open sideways/upward. See Mercedes 300SL "[4]":[/wiki_pages/24728#dtext-external-links] and DeLorean DMC-12 "[5]":[/wiki_pages/24728#dtext-external-links].

title: dudley
body:
A character in the [[Street Fighter]] series. He first appeared in [[Street Fighter III (series)|Street Fighter III]].

Dudley is an English [[boxing|Boxer]] and a refined gentleman. He was born in England to a wealthy family. His father was a former athlete who became a successful businessman. From the time he was a little boy, he wanted to be a fighter but his family told him he was too small to compete. Later, his father lost his business and the family fortune. The losses prompted Dudley to take up professional boxing to earn back lost assets. Dudley then grew into a formidable boxer and was able to bring his family back to affluence. Despite everything that has happened, Dudley still boxes.

title: sengo_muramasa_(touken_ranbu)
body:
A [i][[Touken Ranbu]][/i] character. Based off of an unnamed [[uchigatana]] forged by the original Sengo Muramasa.

A generally soft spoken touken danshi with a polite speech pattern, much like his "brother" sword [[tonbokiri (touken ranbu)|Tonbokiri]]. It's shown in their recollections conversation that Tonbokiri frets over him. Much like [[Yamabushi Kunihiro]], he has a distinctive laugh of "hu hu hu hu" which makes it into most of his lines.

He makes many references to shedding clothes, leading many fans to interpret him as a [[pervert]] or a chronic stripper, much to the ire of Tonbokiri. 

Voiced by [[Suwabe Jun'ichi]]. Character design by [[Namaniku ATK]].

body:
Japanese soft drink apparently made from turmeric"[1]":[/wiki_pages/25611#dtext-external-links]. body:
Profile:
Height: 170cm

A princess from a royal family of high pedigree, originating from the scattered countries of the south. Themis sought help from the Royal Army when she was attacked by monsters. title: daniella_(sennen_sensou_aigis)
body:
Profile:
Height: 165cm
B/W/H: 119/60/91

A dark-skinned archer of a different ethnicity. As Daniela was descended from foreigners, she was seen as an object of curiosity and was picked up by an acrobatic troupe, with whom she traveled between towns again and again. It was at this time that she learned archery. When the demons attacked, the troupe was scattered apart; while she was at loss for what to do, she was helped out by the Prince who she decided to accompany. Knowing that she's predisposed to gaining weight on her chest, she regularly watches what she's eating.

title: umihara_kawase
body:
1994 Super Famicom puzzle platform game featuring a rubber rope with a hook that can attach to walls and ceilings, allowing you to bounce, swing, and fling yourself about acrobatically. Savagely difficult.

There have been sequels and adaptations for the PlayStation, PSP, and NDS, with the 3DS and PS Vita versions seeing release outside Japan.

h4. The name

The characters in the name 海腹川背 mean sea, stomach, river, and back, respectively, and are in reference to the kitchen saying "Sea fish are fat in the belly; river fish are fat in the back."  Umihara is also an existent Japanese surname, but is written with different kanji.

Psikyo (彩京) was a Japanese game developer, founded in 1992, acquired by X-Nauts in mid-2002, and then closed down in 2005. It is the first title in the [b]PROJECT WRITTEN[/b] line of games, and is broken up into episodes called "milestones", and will be released periodically.

[b]fault[/b] follows the story of Princess [[Selphine_Rughzenhaide|Selphine]] of the kingdom Rughzenhaide and her Royal Guard [[Ritona_Reighnvhasta|Ritona]]. The two have accidentally teleported to the furthest side of the planet when trying to flee from an attack that has devastated their homeland.

title: recode_(terra_battle)
body:
Recode DNA is a feature in Terra Battle that can be used to upgrade certain characters to Lambda (Λ) characters. Characters are promoted to a higher class and have a higher stat cap. They will start at level 1, regardless of their level before recoding. Recoded Adventurers will have only one job while monsters will have three (it is the other-way-round before recoding). 

These characters are considered a separate unit, usually with a different character profile that may or may not have references to their pre-recode histories, and may be owned alongside their non-recoded versions.

title: tanzawa-ooyama_quasi-national_park
body:
"Tanzawa-Ōyama Quasi-National Park (丹沢大山国定公園 Tanzawa-Ōyama Kokutei Kōen?) is a quasi-national park in the Kantō region of Honshū in Japan. It is rated a protected landscape (category V) according to the IUCN. The park includes the Tanzawa Mountains, Miyagase Dam and its surrounding forests, Hayato Great Falls and the religious sites of Mount Ōyama in the mountains of western Kanagawa Prefecture." [1]

title: ark_mateus
body:
アーク・マティウス

Main character of [[Shinrabanshou]]'s 2012 storyline, Daimaou to Yattsu no Pillar. As the leader of the Vice demon clan and demon lord of the land of Solomon, he was sealed away by human heroes, but without his power to keep other demons in check the land fell to chaos. Reawakened in the form of a child, Ark fights to regain control and bring peace back to his land.

While Ark is able to retake his old form and throne, he loses his power again in the 2013 storyline, Kuja Senran, while fighting the Jashingun demon swarm invading Solomon. He takes on the role of mentoring the new main character, Apollo, until he is able to regain his strength once more.

Ark wields the two demon swords Gram and Tyrfing, and his special ability is the Ark Strash. When disguised as a human girl, he goes by the name [[ako (shinrabanshou)|Ako]].

title: uguisumaru
body:
A [i][[Touken Ranbu]][/i] character.

One of the Kobizen school swords crafted by Bizen Tomonari. Due to air trapped inside the sword's metal, the blade had many blisters, rendering it useless in battle. Before its presentation to the emperor, they had to fix Uguisumaru in order to make it more presentable. It was since regarded as a work of art rather than something to be used in battle. It was first in the posession of the Ashikaga family, and after Asikaga Yoshinori's awarding it to the Ogasawara family for their participation in the Yuuki Kasen, has been passed down the Ogasawara family line for generations before being given to the Baron Sou family.

Before [[ookanehira_(touken_ranbu)|Ookanehira]] was added into the game, fans took Uguisumaru's mentions of him as Uguisumaru either having an imaginary friend, the other touken danshi thinking he has an imaginary friend, or Ugisumaru being so lonely around the other brother figures like [[Ichigo Hitofuri]] and [[Kousetsu Samonji]] that he talks about Ookanehira more to fit in with them.

An [[original]] character by [[chiwino]]. Has [[long hair|long]] [[black hair]], [[purple eyes]] and [[large breasts]]. Her full name (and the name chiwino uses) is black-haired oppao-san (黒髪のおっぱおさん).

Her name is most likely taken from the word "おっぱお":http://dic.pixiv.net/a/%E3%81%8A%E3%81%A3%E3%81%B1%E3%81%8A (oppao). The word made its first known use on Hikaru Ijuin's radio show Shinya no Barajikara (深夜の馬鹿力) on 11/1/2004 as part of his joke material.

[quote]
子供A「「いっぱい」の「い」を「お」に置き換えて言って見ろ」 
子供B「お・・・おっぱい？」 
子供A「バーカ、おっぱおだよ。おっぱいだって、おまえスケベだな」 

スケベで何が悪い！男は皆、おっぱいが好きなんだ！！（多分） 
[/quote]

Translated:
[quote]
Child A: "Tell me what you get when you replace the 'i' in 'ippai' (a lot) with 'o'."
Child B: "O… 'oppai'?"
Child A: "Duuuumy, you get 'oppao'. Thinking about boobs, you're such a pervert."

[/quote]

title: c_sharp
body:
[[Personification]] of the C# programming language. Related to the [[OS-tan]].


[i]What is C#?[/i]
C# is an object-oriented programming language designed by [[Microsoft]], based on Java and C++ and designed to be portable (although it's actual portability was limited until recently). It's one of the primary languages used on the .NET framework along with C/C++ as well as the primary scripting language in [[unity_(game_engine)|Unity]], powered by Mono.

Mono, an open source implementation of the .NET libraries, allows C# programs to run on platforms other than Microsoft's own. The aquisition of Xamarin (the company who maintained Mono at the time) by Microsoft in March 2016 led to the complete relicensing of Mono to a more permissive license, thus opening C# to a wider range of applications in an even wider range of platforms.

title: java_(programming_language)
body:
Java is an object-oriented, (usually) interpreted programming language renowned for it's portability, being used on almost anything with a CPU. It has a very iconic logo consisting of a stylized coffee mug, being named after Java coffee.

While it had been used in the web in the late 1990's, it's usage waned because of being perceived as slow and insecure.

It's the main programming language used for applications for [[android_(os)|Android]].
